tags: i'm not even that old but i joined the phandom quite young
and it's always quite jarring to remember what it used to be like
summary: i was looking through some of my tags and found an old post about how sad it will be when dnp move out and into separate homes...
body:
i was looking through some of my tags and found an old post about how sad it will be when dnp move out and into separate homes and that post really puts into perspective how much dnp have changed on camera because a few years ago, the thought of them moving out was still plausible. sure, we all knew they were best friends and a lot of us believed they were in a long term relationship, but they weren’t nearly as open on camera as they are now, and we all still had some doubt in our minds and worry about what the future held and whether or not there will be an end to dnp

but now, they’re so much more open and have made it abundantly clear that they’re in this together forever. whether it’s dan saying they’re soulmates in ii or them constantly referring to the future using words like “we” and “us,” we can tell that they don’t have plans to move apart, and it just makes me so happy to look back on how it was a few years ago and be able to see how far they’ve come
